53% of the patients admitted to the home of Victor-Gadbois come from their home, 47% come from the hospital.
Problem of access to palliative care
It is said that 77% of Canadians do not have access to palliative care, i.e. to care that is supposed to alleviate the suffering of patients when the latter have reached the final stage of their lives, both at home, in hospital or in a nursing home.
