It is precisely this great inadequacy in Quebec’s health care that ensures that several physicians specialized in palliative care are looking forward to the adoption of a law regulating euthanasia and assisted suicide with concern.
A manifesto has been circulating since the month of October, which is committed by prominent personalities of palliative care such as Dr. Balfour Mount and Dr. Bernard Lapointe was signed to express her opposition to such an initiative.
Dr. According to Christiane Martel, Quebec's health system is not powerful enough to ensure that everyone has the right to quality palliative care before accepting to passing over to euthanasia.
