The offline private is online private
Privacy
According to the dictionary, this is the property private or "that area of private life where one is entitled to protection from any kind of interference".
What is private for someone under 16 years old?
How is this definition applied to his everyday life and social networks?
Does he understand the dangers he exposes himself to when he makes known on the Internet situations that he would not share in real life?
El Periódico interviewed five young people between the ages of 10 and 15 who frequently travel on the net.
In four of the cases, they linked the term to "something very own" on a personal level and "to the password and the user" when they applied it to the social networks.
"I wouldn't announce my deepest secrets in a post," says 10-year-old Jorge while trying to explain the meaning of "private" in websites like Facebook, Twitter, Hotmail and Windows Live Messenger, where he has had accounts for two years.
